.TH UnixWaitConditions 3 "Oberon System"
.SH NAME
UnixWaitConditions \- conditions for UNIX processes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.Pg
PROCEDURE Create(VAR condition: Conditions.Condition;
                 pid: SysProcess.ProcessId);
.sp 0.7
PROCEDURE FetchStatus(condition: Conditions.Condition;
                      VAR status: SysProcess.Status);
.Pe
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I UnixWaitConditions
offers a cooperative way to wait for child processes to exit.
.I Create
creates a condition which evaluates to \fBTRUE\fP when
the process with the given process id exits.
The status record of an exited process may be retrieved by
.I FetchStatus .
